INSERT INTO `onethink_movie` VALUES ('4230504', 'BBC 音乐的世界系列-贝多芬', null, 'http://movie.douban.com/subject/4230504/', 'null', '9.0', '2005', 'movie', '1398408444', '0', '0', '　　This series was made as a result of the BBC\'s hugely successful and popular series \"The Genius of Mozart\". Both series follow the same format, a cross between a drama and a documentary (docudrama), each series is made of three episodes of an hour each, and each is mixed with insightful pieces of narration by the popular conductor/composer/presenter Charles Hazlewood.\n                                    \n                                　　\"The Genius of Mozart\" was a big hit for the BBC, attracting masses of enthusiastic viewers of all walks of life. With this in mind you would think that a similar programme based on Beethoven would attract a similarly popular response. However this was not the case. This series was not viewed by a large audience, there have been no repeats or DVD releases and I was shocked to visit it\'s IMDb page to discover there were absolutely no user comments, (I write this now wondering if it will ever be read).\n                                    \n                                　　In brief, I remember watching this series and being absolutely blown away, It was so powerful I can still remember it in detail. In my opinion it is amongst the best work the BBC have ever produced and I am extremely saddened that very few people experienced the same joy I did from this series. I think \"Beethoven\" has become a lost gem and I will use the remainder of this user comment to argue my case.\n                                    \n                                　　The series was beautifully photographed and directed. The series was filled with a beautifully desaturated palette (with a prominent ochre for interior scenes) which gave a stark, imposing temperament. Along with this there were wonderful intersections with diffuses of aged yet colourful soft focus imagery, giving a romantic yet nostalgic feel, like a lost love. It was a breathtaking contrast of these romantic diffuses with desaturated scenes, to me it evoked Beethoven\'s isolation and difficulty to keep a grip on reality.\n                                    \n                                　　The story and dialogue was fantastically well written. It powerfully evoked the turmoil, isolation and despair of Beethoven. It was a highly accurate historical portrayal along with a caliber and sophistication of writing which seemed to transcend it\'s historical obligations giving a highly emotional, gritty and moving experience.', '0');
INSERT INTO `onethink_movie` VALUES ('3190809', '贝多芬住我家楼上', null, 'http://movie.douban.com/subject/3190809/', 'null', '9.0', '', 'movie', '1398408444', '0', '0', '　　《Beethoven Lives Upstairs》译作「贝多芬住在楼上」，内容主要讲述贝多芬与住在楼下的小童如何建立友谊关系，由於贝多芬行为古怪，初期难与小童成友，及后贝多芬慢慢步向失聪时，却获小童相赠已去世父亲的助听器，因而成了知己，两人更在《欢乐颂》(第九交响曲中选段)互相讨论音乐，情景甚为感人。可让儿童认识一位音乐伟人和他的事迹，这确是好教材。\n                                    \n                                　　故事讲述一个小孩子的父亲去世后，与母亲相依为命，把居住的楼房二楼租给了一个音乐家，他就是性情古怪，个性暴燥的作曲家贝多芬。孩子的母亲懂得弹钢琴，叔叔又是小提琴家，因此对音乐家有一份好奇及尊敬的心，他很想和这邻居沟通。但贝多芬的行为往往不近人情，在居所内不修边幅，甚至「无上装」随屋走，成盆洗面水拿起照头淋，令到全地都湿，做成不少滋扰，但楼下的一家人基於尊敬他是位知名音乐家都只好忍受和加以同情。\n                                    \n                                　　这阶段贝多芬耳疾加剧，要靠文字来与人沟通，小孩子的父亲是个医生，遗下了一个助听器，他就找出来送给贝多芬，这一来令这位音乐家大受感动，他们从此成为好朋友。内容同时涉及他写作第九交响曲中「欢乐颂」的过程，从彩排到演出，正式演出时由他上台只作状指挥，因那时他已完全失聪，实际上，在台下由另一人真正领导演出，所以在演完后，受到观众热鼓掌喝采时，贝多芬仍蒙然不知，继续指下去，直至乐队团员拉他转身谢幕才惊觉！这事迹贝多芬的传记亦有提及，场面十分感人。贝多芬的扮相神似，而母子两个角色亦演得入戏，电影拍得很有时代气氛，看来亦有趣味性。\n                                    \n                                　　——————————————\n                                    \n                                　　引自baidu：\n                                    \n                                　　http://zhidao.baidu.com/question/50509182.html', '0');
